The Russian experience
------------------------
It is difficult to [document the scientific [basis for the practice of
controlling outbreaks of aseptic meningitis in children by the prophylactic
use of poliovirus vaccine. Nonetheless, the use of poliovaccine against
enteroviral meningitis in the former Soviet Union has [significantly
decreased the risk of disease and [succeded in localizing outbreaks.
Probably this is connected with the [interactions, which exist between
enteroviruses. Indeed this approach has been used [successfully for a long
period of time by physicians in the Far East region of Russia.
